w:r.w:t: Example Word XML Document with a Custom XML Part
Custom XML parts can be added to any word document by using the XML Mapping Pane in the Developers tab in MS Word. This allows for “linking/data binding” of content controls.
Content controls can then be inserted based on the custom xml part:
THESE TYPES OF CONTENT CONTROLS CAN ALL BE LINKED:
Simple single or multiple paragraph. Can be linked with Combo boxes and dropdown list.
